AMARILLO OIL COMPANY v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE. No. 1204. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Dec. 31, 1934. H. B. McCawley, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. Robert H. Jackson, Asst. Gen. Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petition for review dismissed for failure to prosecute.
